Proposed component architecture for the new frontend, based on deep reverse-engineering of frontend_old, without implementation.

**1. Folder Structure**

| Folder | Responsibility | Minimal scalable contents |
|---|---|---|
| /components/ui | Atomic primitives and style-safe building blocks | button.tsx, badge.tsx, input.tsx, checkbox.tsx, tabs.tsx, card.tsx, modal.tsx, spinner.tsx, index.ts |
| /components/shared | Cross-page composites built from ui primitives | page-container.tsx, section-shell.tsx, app-header.tsx, app-footer.tsx, floating-section-nav.tsx, match-card.tsx, status-badge.tsx, premium-gate.tsx, payment-modal.tsx, empty-state.tsx, error-state.tsx, social-link.tsx, index.ts |
| /components/sections | Route-level section assemblies only | landing/hero-section.tsx, landing/auth-cta-section.tsx, landing/social-section.tsx, dashboard/welcome-section.tsx, dashboard/for-you-section.tsx, dashboard/expert-analysis-section.tsx, dashboard/coming-soon-section.tsx, matches/matches-hero-section.tsx, matches/matches-tabs-section.tsx, matches/matches-grid-section.tsx, index.ts |

Design rule: ui has no domain logic, shared has reusable domain-light logic, sections contains domain-aware page chunks.

---

**2. Component Hierarchy**

1. Atomic components in /components/ui  
Button, Badge, Input, Checkbox, Tabs, Card, ModalBase, Spinner.

2. Composite components in /components/shared  
SectionShell, PageContainer, AppHeader, AppFooter, FloatingSectionNav, MatchCard, PremiumGate, PaymentModal, StatusBadge, EmptyState, ErrorState.

3. Section components in /components/sections  
Landing sections, Dashboard sections, Matches sections.

4. Route pages compose sections only  
Pages should orchestrate data and section order, not render primitive markup directly.

Route composition target:
- / uses Landing sections only.
- /dashboard and /dashboard-new use Dashboard sections + FloatingSectionNav.
- /matches uses Matches sections + shared shell components.
- /dashboard-old can be handled through an optional legacy adapter module if needed later.

---

**3. Naming Conventions**

- Component names: PascalCase.
- File names: kebab-case.
- Props interfaces: ComponentNameProps.
- Sections always end with Section.
- Reusable card-like composites end with Card.
- Dialogs end with Modal.
- Domain state wrappers end with Container only when they own fetch/state.
- Avoid old versus enhanced suffixes in new architecture. Use folder scoping and variant props instead.
- Use variant, size, tone props for styling differences rather than duplicating components.

---

**4. Props Design (Clean + Reusable)**

- Every ui and shared component accepts className.
- Visual components use a constrained variant API: variant, size, tone, disabled.
- Controlled pattern for interactive components:
  - Tabs: value, onValueChange
  - Modal: open, onOpenChange
  - Inputs: value, onChange
- Async-aware sections use a unified state shape:
  - loading, error, data, onRetry
- Event props are intention-based, not DOM-based:
  - onUpgrade, onSelectMatch, onOpenDetails, onSubscribe
- Data components receive typed domain objects, not many loose scalar props.
- Avoid boolean explosion. Prefer enums or variant unions where states are mutually exclusive.
- Keep page sections shallow: sections get prepared data from page-level hooks, not direct API clients.

